x4freetext: Correction in Some Subentries.
Total Fission Cross Section is Included.
Last checking has been done.
DATE is corrected
.Cascade Calculations.
.Four Ge(LI) Detectors.None of the Nuclides were
Measured on Only a Nai-Detector and Most of the Results
Are Determined with at Least Two Detectors.
The Detectors were Coupled to Different Amplifier and
Multichannel Analyzer Systems.
Number of Determinations.
The Stack Consisted of a Target Foil of Pb 99.999%
0.5 mm Thick with Catcher Foils of 30 Mum Aluminium,
Monitor Foils of 10 Mum Al and Guard Foils of 30 Mum
Aluminium on Both Sides.
.Rb was Separated from the Target Solution by a
Perchlorate Precipitation and Futher Purified by a
Series of Hydroxide-,Sulfide- And Carbonate-Scavengings
To Remove Contamination.
.The Uncertainty is Reported by Authors.
The Errors are Standard Deviations Based on Errors in
Gamma-Peak Area Analysis,Counting Efficiencies and
Counting Statistics,Chemical Yield Measurements Monitor
Cross Section,and Spread Among the Parallel
Determinations.Errors in the Half-Lives and Absolute
Gamma-Ray Intensities are not Included.

x4freetext: Number of Determinations.
Dauther of Kr-76.
Dauther of Kr-88.
Dauther of Kr-89.
A Target Consisted of 343 G Molten Lead of High Purity.
Energy Spread For this Target is 62. MeV was Calculated
By Authors.
The Arrival Time on the Collectors.
The Isolde Facility.
The Target Cylinder is Kept in an Oven in Vacuum and at
A Temperature of About 700 Centigrad. It is Connected
Via a Steel Tube at Approximately Room Temperature to
An Isotope Separator Ion Source. Primery Constructed
For the Production of Mercury Isotopes, the Target Also
Evaporates the Volatile Fission Products Kr and Xe. By
Changing the Field of the Isotope Separator Magnet One
Can Then Choose What Mass Region to Study. In the
Collector Chamber of the Isotope Separator, One May
Collect the Isotoped Separated by Letting the Ion Beams
Hit a Horizontal Aluminium Foil Strip Placed
Perpendicularly to the Central Mass Beam.
The Foils is Mounted in a Holder That May be
Lowered from a Shielded Position Above the Plane of the
Ion Beams, Such That the Ions May be Collected During
A Chosen Time Interval. After Collection, the Strip is
Switched Out of the Beam and Withdrawn from the
Collector Tank Through an Air Lock.By Cutting the
Aluminium Foil Between the Positions of the Masses,Each
Isotope can be Counted by Mounting the Pieces in
Standard Sample Holders.
.The Uncertainty is Reported by Authors.
The Errors are Here Only Due to the Gamma-Spectrum
Analysis and the Spread Among the Different Runs.
